title: PMLN Candidate Jalat wins PK-08 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PMLN) Jalat has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-08, Swat-VI by securing 15,007 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Awaami National Party (ANP) candidate Iftekhar Ahmed who bagged 11,289 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 34.05 per cent.
